    "intro": "Interpretation asks what the text means — moving from observation to the author's intent and the chapter's canonical significance. The movements below trace the chapter's argument from Joab's political engineering through David's fatal half-measure. The Succession Narrative (2 Sam 9-20) is theological history: it traces the outworking of Nathan's judgment (12:10-12) in the domestic catastrophe of David's house. Chapter 14 is a crucial link in that chain.",
